🐟Tin Fish Review🐟 Tsar Nicolai trout roe, $20 Flavor: 🤯 Texture: 🤯 Value: 🤯 Scale: 🙁😐🙂😍🤯 I  previously reviewed Trader Joe’s smoked Trout, so feel free to check out the full write up in my post history. Summary is it’s a very solid entry level tin at a fantastic price ($4). It’s especially well suited for mixing with creamy ingredients for a dip or sandwich spread.  Today I want to talk about one of my favorite fishy treats: trout roe, aka cured trout eggs. Trout roe are smaller and more mild than salmon roe (or ikura), so I think it’s a perfect “first time” roe to try. At around $10-25 per ounce, it’s a much more accessible caviar alternative, but still adds a touch of luxury to whatever you pair with it.  Salmon eggs are large and bring a big, bold, fishy flavor when they pop. Trout roe, on the other hand, provide much more of a subtle “pop,” followed by a rush of lovely oceanic salinity with a touch of sweetness.  I can’t say that @therealtsarnicoulai trout roe tastes particularly different than others I have tried, but that’s a great considering their price is competitive and they are a local california business focusing on sustainability (which def isn’t the norm in the world of caviar).  Usually I enjoy trout roe with just creme fraiche on a baguette (heaven), but trout dip with trout roe is a classic combination as well. I actually made this video last week and then picked up a copy of @ahezel ‘s book Tin to Table and saw she also has her version of trout dip in her book as well (check that one out if you want exact measurements!) In my version, I used shallot, dill, parsley, creme fraiche, mayo, horseradish, and lemon, but feel free to play with the ingredients you have on hand. Grab the potato chips and enjoy! #tinnedfish #cannedseafood #cannedfood #caviar #traderjoes

EPISODE 4: Koobideh Kebab bowl  To make:  1. Put one onion im a food processer/blender till its a smooth chunky paste and then run it through a sieve over a bowl to get all the water out. The onion water will collect in the bowl below. Discard the onion water.  2. Add the onion paste to 1 lb of ground beef (20% fat is best for juicy kebabs) and add 1-2 tablespoons of sumac, and salt. (Optional: add a grated garlic clove. You dont need to bc the onion puree adds so much flavor & juice! Trust the process). Mix until seasonings are combined.  3. Spray the air fryer with avocado oil, take the grounf beef mixture directlh into your hands and shape into logs in the air fryer directly. You can shape it in the air fryer since the mixture may be a bit soft and hard to form into logs beforehand. It will solidify while cooking!  4. Cook for 10 min at 410. 5. Brush with melted butter after and serve with grilled veggies, greek salad, zaatar pita, and hummus :)

EP 1: Cindy’s Soups, Stews & Curries 🍜 1. Dice shallots, ginger, garlic, and thai chillies and saute your aromatics with a little sesame oil.  2. Add 1-2 tablespoons of white miso and let it get nice and toasty  3. Add your longer cooking veggies - think carrots, any root veggies and add coconut milk  4. Whisk in the miso so it gets blended into the sauce.  5. (Optional): I add lime leaves but fine to leave out. Just dont forget to add the lemon/lime at the end!  5. Bring to a boil and then let it reduce down to a simmer. Add your veggies (i did zucchini, yellow squash, eggplant & oyster mushrooms) and poach whatever seafood you want to use- clams, shrimp, white fish, etc.,. Cover with a lid for 5-7 minutes.  6. Sometimes ill sear my fish and scallops seperately.  7. KEY: add a generous squeeze of lime or lemon to the curry towards the end. This really brings out the flavor and is SO IMPORTANT since this curry relies on a few key ingredients.  8. Garnish with cilantro and serve with rice. Being unable to wear cute shoes due to sweaty feet is a definite downside. However, it is truly the least of the concerns for someone who suffers from Plantar Hyperhidrosis.  Constantly having sweaty feet can lead to much more severe issues, such as skin irritation and bacteria build-up, which can ultimately lead to fungus.  You somewhat have to ‘pick your battles’—do you wear sandals and let your feet have air, but risk sliding around in your shoes all day? Or do you wear sneakers and trap the moisture inside for hours on end?  Luckily, there is an option where you don’t have to choose between sliding around and irritated skin. Dr. Basseri at The Center for Hyperhidrosis is the ONLY surgeon in the United States that offers a procedure specifically for Plantar hyperhidrosis (excessively sweaty feet). If you would like more information on the ELS procedure with Dr. Basseri, please reach out to us via direct message, and our team will personally connect with you.  #hyperhidrosisawareness #hyperhidrosiscommunity #hyperhidrosis #sweaty #excessivesweating #sweatyfeet

welcome back to my series where I’m turning a single $55 grocery list into your week of easy, healthy meals — this is recipe #1! 💕 if you’re new here, I post one recipe per day all week and all of them are gluten & dairy free and serve 3-4 people! the entire grocery list is in the caption of the previous video 😊  full recipe is below & also on my website!  ingredients: - 1/4 cup olive oil  - 3/4 large yellow onion, diced - 2-3 large carrots, diced  - 10oz sliced white mushrooms - 4 garlic cloves, minced - 1-2 tsp salt + more as needed - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1 tsp dried thyme - 2 tbsp cornstarch, arrowroot starch, or tapioca starch - 1/2 cup nutritional yeast - 3 + 1/4 cups vegetable broth - 1/2 cup water, plus more as needed - 2 tbsp coconut aminos or tamari - 1 cup wild rice, thoroughly rinsed - 1 heaping cup shredded kale - 1/2 15oz can full-fat coconut milk, shaken heat the olive oil over medium heat in a large pot, then add the diced onion and carrots. cook the onion and carrots, stirring periodically, for 10 minutes or until the onions are translucent, then add in the sliced mushrooms and minced garlic. stir and cook for another 10 minutes. mix in the salt, black pepper, and thyme and let the spices get aromatic, about 3-5 minutes. add in the starch and mix well to incorporate it into the vegetables. do the same with the nutritional yeast. pour in all of the vegetable broth, 1/2 cup of water, coconut aminos, and rinsed wild rice. put a lid on the pot and bring the soup to a boil. once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 40-55 minutes, stirring occasionally. once the rice is fully cooked, mix in the shredded kale and coconut milk.  allow the kale to wilt, then serve immediately or simmer over low heat until serving. store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to five days or in the freezer for up to a month. I hope you love it! i’ll be back tomorrow 🫶 #budgetshopping #groceriesonabudget #groceryshopping #groceryshop #groceryhaul #mealprep #mealprepping #mealprepideas #grocerylist #mealsonabudget #healthyonabudget #easyhealthyrecipes #glutenfreerecipes #dairyfreerecipes #traderjoes

the final day of this week’s series where I turned a $55 grocery trip into 5 easy, healthy gluten-free & dairy-free dinners for this week 💕 finishing off the week with a delish kale & chicken salad perfect for fall 🍂  full recipe is below & also on my website!   maple rosemary chicken:  - 2 lb boneless chicken thighs - 2 tbsp + 1/3 cup olive oil - 1 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp pepper - 1/2 tsp garlic powder  - 2 tbsp maple syrup - 1 tsp dried rosemary - 1 tsp dried thyme maple vinaigrette:  - 1/2 cup olive oil - 1/4 cup coconut aminos - 2 tbsp maple syrup - 1 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1/2 tsp dried thyme - 1/2 tsp dried rosemary - 1/2 tsp garlic powder kale salad:  - 4-6 heaping cups shredded kale - 1 + 1/2 - 2 cups butternut squash, cubed + seeds reserved (optional) & olive oil, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder for baking - 2-4 carrots, finely chopped - 8-10 dates, pitted and finely chopped - 2 tbsp fresh chopped rosemary or 2 tsp dried rosemary - 1 cup dry wild rice, cooked according to package instructions preheat oven to 375 & line a large & small sheet pan with parchment. add the squash/oil/salt/pepper/garlic (and seeds if desired) to the small pan and the chicken, 2 tbsp oil/salt/pepper/garlic to the large. place both in the oven. whisk together remaining 1/3 cup of olive oil, maple syrup, rosemary, and thyme for the maple rosemary chicken thighs. after 25 mins, remove both pans. set squash aside. cover the chicken in the maple rosemary sauce and place back in the oven for 10 minutes to finish baking. mix all vinaigrette ingredients in a bowl or jar. massage into the kale using tongs or clean hands and let sit at least 10 mins. when the chicken is done (165 degrees) slice it up. assemble the salad by adding the squash and seeds, diced carrots, chopped dates, and rosemary to the kale. mix in the chicken. serve in large bowls with a scoop of cooked wild rice on top and enjoy!! this is my series where I’m turning a single $55 grocery list into 5 easy, healthy gluten-free & dairy-free dinners for this week — each recipe serves 3-4 people & this is recipe #4! 💕 today we’re making the easiest sheet pan tofu ever!! full recipe is below & also on my website!   crispy tofu & carrots: - 14oz firm tofu - 3-4 large carrots, sliced + salt, pepper, & garlic powder to season - 2 tbsp cornstarch, arrowroot starch, or tapioca starch - 1/4 cup olive oil - 1 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1 tsp garlic powder - 1 cup dry wild rice, cooked according to package instructions - 3 green onions, sliced - 1 tbsp sesame seeds (optional) maple rosemary sauce:  - 1/3 cup coconut aminos or tamari - 1/4 cup maple syrup - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1/2 tsp dried thyme - 1/2 tsp dried rosemary preheat your oven to 350 degrees and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. press your tofu in your preferred way (I wrap it in paper towels, then place it on a plate and put a heavy pan or press on top) for 20-30 minutes to remove the moisture. slice the carrots, then cut the tofu into cubes once it's done being pressed. in a bowl, combine the cubed tofu, starch, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder. use clean hands to coat all of the tofu in the starch and spices. add the sliced carrots to the sheet pan and toss in the olive oil and additional salt, black pepper, and garlic powder. add the tofu to the pan and spread out the carrots and tofu evenly. bake for 20-25 minutes, until the tofu is browning and carrots are tender. while it bakes, whisk together all of the sauce ingredients in a small bowl. pour the sauce over the tofu and carrots and use a spatula to coat them in the sauce. place back in the oven for 10-20 minutes, until crisp and caramelizing. serve the tofu and carrots with the cooked wild rice, top with the sliced green onions and sesame seeds and enjoy. store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to five days. #budgetshopping #groceriesonabudget #groceryshopping #groceryshop #groceryhaul #mealprep #mealprepping #mealprepideas #grocerylist #mealsonabudget #healthyonabudget #easyhealthyrecipes #glutenfreerecipes #dairyfreerecipes #traderjoes #sheetpanmeals #tofurecipe #fallrecipes

welcome back to my series where I’m turning a single $55 grocery list into 5 easy, healthy gluten-free & dairy-free meals — each recipe serves 3-4 people & this is recipe #3! 💕 this week I’m featuring my favorite fall flavors and cozy dishes, and the entire grocery list is in the caption of the first video. I hope you enjoy!!  full recipe is below & also on my website!   ingredients:  - 1/4 cup olive oil - 1/4 large yellow onion, diced - 1 + 1/2 - 2 cups butternut squash, cubed - 1 lb ground pork - 1 tsp salt + more as needed to taste - 1/2 tsp black pepper + more as needed to taste - 3 garlic cloves, minced or 1 tsp garlic powder - 1 tsp dried thyme - 1/2 tsp dried rosemary - 1/4 tsp ground sage + 1/4 tsp ground sage - 1 heaping cup shredded kale - 3/4 cup vegetable broth - 1/2 15oz can full-fat coconut milk, shaken (note this is a thin sauce, if you want it super saucy I would recommend going for a whole can) - 1/2 cup nutritional yeast - 12oz gluten-free pasta of choice, cooked according to package instructions heat the oil over medium heat in a large skillet, then add the onion and butternut squash. cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, then add in the ground pork. break apart the pork with a spatula and let cook for another 10-15 minutes, until the pork is fully browned and the onion is translucent. meanwhile, fully cook your pasta. mix in the salt, pepper, garlic, thyme, rosemary, and 1/4 tsp of sage to the pork mixture and let the spices get aromatic, about 5 minutes. incorporate the shredded kale to the mix and let it wilt. remove the pork mixture from the skillet and set aside. in the same skillet, add the vegetable broth and coconut milk and bring to a simmer. stir in the remaining 1/4 tsp of sage and nutritional yeast, and season with additional salt and black pepper. reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes. add the pasta to the skillet and mix to cover all the pasta in sauce. add the pork mixture and stir to incorporate. store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to four days or in the freezer for up to a month. enjoy!! I’m turning a single $55 grocery list into your week of easy, healthy dinners ideas — this is recipe #2 of 5! 💕 I post one recipe per day and all of them are gluten & dairy free and serve 3-4! grocery list is in the caption of the first video 😊  veggie sheet pan: 2 + 1/2 cups cubed butternut squash (about half of a large one) 2 large carrots, cut in ~1/4 inch slices 1/4 cup olive oil 1 + 1/2 tsp salt 1/2 tsp black pepper 1 lb brussels sprouts, halved ~8-10 dates, pitted and finely chopped 1/2 tsp rosemary (dried or fresh finely chopped) 1/2 tsp dried thyme 1/2 tsp garlic powder (can sub for fresh minced) maple rosemary chicken thighs: 2 lb boneless skinless chicken thighs 2 tbsp + 1/3 cup olive oil 1 tsp salt 1/2 tsp black pepper 1/2 tsp garlic powder (can sub for fresh minced) 2 tbsp maple syrup 1 tsp rosemary (dried or fresh finely chopped) 1 tsp dried thyme preheat oven to 375 and line two large sheet pans with parchment. to the first, add your squash and carrots along with the oil, salt, and black pepper. cover the vegetables in the oil/spices and bake for 20 minutes.  meanwhile, add the chicken, 2 tbsp of oil, salt, pepper, & garlic to the second sheet pan. cover all of the chicken in the oil and spices. add the chicken to the oven and bake for 25 minutes.  after cooking the squash & carrots for 20 minutes, remove it from the oven and add the brussels sprouts, dates, rosemary, thyme, & garlic powder. mix to combine & place back in the oven for 15-20 minutes, until the vegetables are browning and crisp. in a bowl, whisk together the remaining 1/3 cup olive oil, maple syrup, rosemary, and thyme. when the chicken has baked for 25 minutes, remove it from the oven and pour the maple sauce over it. cover the chicken in the sauce and place it back in the oven for 10 minutes. when it’s done and at a temp of 165 degrees, slice it up (if you're following my series, set aside half of the cooked chicken for another recipe), then plate it with the veggies and enjoy. homemade almond joy candy bars 🫶🏼 they’re gluten free, dairy free, paleo, and refined sugar free, and taste so much like the real thing! ingredients •2 cups unsweetened coconut flakes/shreds •1/4 cup raw honey or pure maple syrup •1/4 cup coconut oil •1/4 cup full fat canned coconut milk •6oz dark or semi-sweet chocolate (i use dairy free) instructions 1. first, melt the coconut oil. next, make the coconut filling: add the shredded coconut, coconut milk, honey/maple syrup, and melted coconut oil to a food processor and process for about a minute, scraping down the sides as needed. 2. once smooth, add the filling to an 8x5 loaf pan lined with parchment paper and smooth it out. next, top with roasted almonds (be sure to press the almonds down into the coconut mixture). 3. place in the freezer to harden for several hours. once frozen, remove the from the freezer and slice into 12 bars. 4. next, melt your chocolate. once melted, coat each bar in melted chocolate and place on a tray lined with parchment paper. place in the fridge to harden for several hours. 5. once hardened, remove from the fridge and enjoy! store in the fridge or freezer. who’s giving these a try?😍 #almondjoys #almondjoy #almondjoybar #almondjoybars #homemadealmondjoy  #moundsbars #moundscandybar  #homemadecandybar #homemadecandy #almondjoyrecipe  #healthyalmondjoy  #healthymoundsbar #glutenfreedessert #dairyfreedessert #paleodessert #grainfreedessert #refinedsugarfree #healthydessert #vegandessert #veganmoundsbar #veganchocolate #easyrecipe #easydessert #easyhealthyrecipes #bountybars

I’m back turning $50 of groceries into a week of easy, healthy meals! they’re all gluten & dairy free, and you can grab the entire grocery list from the caption of the last video 🤝🛒 I’m kicking it off with a shockingly simple but SO delicious lemony chicken and rice bake — the full recipe is below! 🍋 ingredients: - 2 tbsp olive or avocado oil - 1 lb boneless chicken thighs - 1 + 1/2 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 2 tsp smoked paprika - 2 tsp italian seasoning - 1/4 yellow onion, chopped - 3 garlic cloves, minced - 1 cup of white rice - 1 lemon, juiced - 1 cup chicken broth - 1/2 of 15oz can full-fat coconut milk - 2 cups chopped kale - up to 1 + 1/2 cups water, as needed - 1/3 cup fresh chopped parsley preheat oven to 375 degrees and drizzle the olive oil on a large skillet over medium heat on the stovetop.  pat the chicken thighs dry with a paper towel, then season all over with the salt, black pepper, smoked paprika, and italian seasoning. transfer the chicken to the pan when the olive oil is heated.  cook the chicken to crisp each side, about 5-7 minutes on each side depending on thickness, then set aside on a plate. in the same pan, add the chopped onion and sauté for 5 minutes, then add the minced garlic.  when the onion and garlic are translucent, pour in the rice and let it toast for a few minutes, stirring frequently. add in the lemon juice, chicken broth, and coconut milk and mix to combine.  add in all of the chopped kale and let it wilt down. add up to 1 + 1/2 cups of water as needed to wilt down the kale and make sure all of the rice is covered in liquid. transfer to the oven and bake for 15-20 minutes, until the rice is fully cooked and the chicken has an internal temp of 165 degrees.  serve immediately or store the chicken and rice in airtight containers in the fridge for up to 4 days. enjoy!! turning $50 of groceries into 10(+) easy, healthy meals 💞🥰 they’re all gluten free + dairy free!! and this one is plant based! follow along this week, I’ll post one recipe per day! ✨ recipe 1 is below! ingredients: - 1 english cucumber, sliced  - ~3 green onions, chopped - ~2/3 cup fresh chopped cilantro - 1 lb edamame beans (I used frozen) - 1 + 1/4 cup shredded carrots - 1 cup quinoa (cooked with 2 cups of veggie broth according to package instructions) - 3 tbsp olive oil dressing: - 1/4 cup sesame oil  - 1 tbsp rice vinegar - 2 tbsp coconut aminos - 1 tbsp maple syrup  - 1/4 cup peanut butter - 1 tsp garlic powder - 1 tbsp ground ginger  - salt & pepper to taste preheat oven to 350 degrees and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. add the cooked quinoa (cooked based on package instructions with veggie broth instead of water) and spread it out evenly on the pan. toss with the olive oil and season with salt & pepper if desired. bake for 35 minutes, stirring halfway through.  make the dressing by combining all ingredients in a jar and shaking until it’s a uniform consistency. chop up all veggies.  when the quinoa is done, all it to a large bowl with all of the chopped veggies and the dressing, mix well and serve immediately or store in airtight containers in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.  enjoy!! full grocery list is in the caption of my first video! #budgetshopping #groceriesonabudget #groceryshopping #groceryshop #groceryhaul #mealprep #mealprepping #mealprepideas #grocerylist #mealsonabudget #healthyonabudget #easyhealthyrecipes #traderjoes

Healing Hashimotos Autoimmune Journey. I like to say healing! Just bc i have this forever doesnt mean I cant feel healing and be in healing within my body. I still have a long way to go to where I want to be. But I am happy how far ive come.  ➡️ I share everything ive learned in my Healing Hashimotos Membeeship launching in May - link in profile #hashimotosthyroiditis #hashimotos #hashimotossymptoms #healinghashimotos #functionaldietitian #antiinflammatory #hormonebalance

When I was diagnosed with Hashimoto’s, I was told that this was a condition that likely would not improve. I remember feeling really defeated because I finally had a *why* behind why I was experiencing certain symptoms, but being told it would probably never get better was really discouraging. I was experiencing stubborn weight gain (even though I was SO focused on healthy eating and consistent exercise), chronic fatigue, and was always bloated. I had to take control of my health and advocate for myself, requesting additional lab work for antibodies, hormone health and more. I had to do a ton of research on nutrition strategies that could help thyroid function and created a plan for myself that combined anti-inflammatory, hormone-supporting foods and nutrients. When I made the correct changes, I finally started to feel better- within *days* I was less bloated, within months I was losing weight and my thyroid function improved. I continue to monitor my thyroid antibodies and have since added back in dairy. These nutrition strategies were in combination with thyroid medication! Without nutrition changes and medication only, my TSH was 18, so the diet is definitely making a difference here. Just sharing my health story and what has worked for me! #thyroidhealth #thyroidweightloss #hashimotosweightloss #weightlosstipsforwomen #weightlosstips #dietitiantips

What is Hashimoto’s?  Hashimoto’s thyroiditis is an autoimmune condition that results when the immune system attacks the thyroid tissues. In this situation, the immune system mistakes thyroid cells for unfamiliar invaders and launches an inflammatory response directed to destroy pathogens.  Over time, this destruction results in progressive hypothyroidism, or low thyroid activity. Although thyroid antibodies are often untested in those exhibiting hypothyroid symptoms, researchers suspect approximately 90% of low thyroid sufferers have autoimmune thyroiditis, most of whom are women. This is an important statistic because effective treatment for autoimmunity is vastly different than the standard protocol for low thyroid. For the millions of people suffering from autoimmune-induced low thyroid that are being treated with thyroid replacement therapy, alone, a degenerative disease is manifesting under the surface that will eventually cause debilitating and far-reaching symptoms.  Although Hashimoto’s is widely agreed upon in conventional and functional medicine circles to be the number one cause of low thyroid, most patients are not thoroughly tested for this condition. Because low thyroid symptoms are easily mistaken for other conditions, this disease is often overlooked, and patients are either misdiagnosed or told that it is all in their head and to go home.  How serious is Hashimoto’s disease?  Thyroid function is complex and involves a relationship between the pituitary gland, hypothalamus, and thyroid glands. However, adrenal glands and other systems throughout the body play a role in a healthy thyroid. The best way to identify the root cause of your thyroid imbalance is with proper testing. The problem with conventional approaches to thyroid, is in large part, the lack of essential testing. Most practitioners only test biproducts of the pituitary and thyroid glands. However, that approach does not consider countless other indicators of a damaged thyroid hormone process. caramelized onion & herb buttered noodles!  Ingredients: 1/2 lb pasta 2 tbsp olive oil 2 yellow onions, sliced thin 1 tbsp fresh thyme 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar 1 stick butter, softened salt and pepper to taste as many fresh herbs as you want! (i used a small handful of basil, tarragon, chives, and parsley) Instructions: Heat oil in a large sauté pan over med/low heat. Add onions and cook for about 30 minutes or so, stirring occasionally until the onions are jammy and brown. Add thyme, balsamic vinegar, salt, and pepper. Stir (making sure to scape the bottom of the pan!) and let cook for a few more minutes, then set aside to cool. While onions cool, cook the pasta according to package instructions. Be sure to save some pasta water.  Add butter, caramelized onions, and whatever herbs you want to a food processor. Pulse until everything is well combined.  Toss the butter mixture with the cooked hot pasta and a little pasta water. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. Top with parm (optional but highly recommended) and enjoy. #caramelizedonions #pasta #easyrecipe #pastatok

Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) exercises have proven to be effective in enhancing flexibility in one's thinking style. This therapeutic approach, developed by prominent psychologists, focuses on identifying and challenging negative thought patterns and replacing them with more balanced and realistic ones. CBT exercises help individuals recognize cognitive distortions, such as black-and-white thinking or catastrophizing, which can limit their ability to see alternative perspectives. By engaging in structured exercises, individuals are encouraged to examine the evidence supporting their beliefs and explore alternative explanations. This process promotes cognitive flexibility by loosening rigid thought patterns and opening up possibilities for different interpretations. CBT exercises also involve experimenting with new behaviors and examining their outcomes, allowing individuals to challenge their assumptions and develop more adaptive ways of thinking. Through repetition and practice, individuals can gradually shift their thinking style, becoming more open-minded, adaptable, and resilient in the face of challenges. This increased flexibility in thinking enables individuals to approach situations with a broader perspective, consider multiple solutions, and effectively adapt to changing circumstances. Ultimately, CBT exercises empower individuals to break free from cognitive rigidity, leading to improved mental well-being and a more fulfilling life.  #therapytok #therapistsontiktok #therapytools #cbt #journalideas

one pot broccoli cheddar pasta 🥦🧀🥦🧀 easy, cheesy, and kind of nostalgic-y because of the spaghettios vibe  recipe: 2 tbsp butter 1 tbsp olive oil 2 cloves garlic, minced 1 shallot, minced  1 medium carrot, shredded (about 3/4 cup shredded) 2 cups broccoli 2 cups anelli pasta 4 cups water or broth 1/2 tsp paprika 1/2 tsp black pepper 1/2 tsp garlic powder salt to taste 1/2 cup heavy cream 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese Melt butter and oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add shallot and garlic and cook until fragrant. Add carrot and pasta and cook for a couple minutes. Add water (or broth) and spices and bring to a boil. Turn down the heat to a simmer and cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until most of the water is absorbed. Add broccoli, heavy cream, and cheese, stir until the cheese is melted. Continue to cook for about 5 more minutes, until pasta is al dente and sauce is thick. Serve immediately.  #pasta #broccolicheddar #easyrecipe #pastatok

Buttermilk Saffron pancakes with gulab jamun  🌹Dry Ingredients  - 1 1/3 cup of flour  - 1tsp salt  - 2 tbs sugar  - 1 tbs baking powder  - 1/2 tsp baking soda (for that rise) 🌹Wet ingredients  (Everything needs to be at room temp)  - 1 cup buttermilk / 1 cup milk + 1 tbs lemon juice (let it sit for 15 mins) - 8-10 Saffron soaked in the buttermilk  - 1 egg  - 4 tbs melted butter  - 0.25 tsp cardamom powder  🌹Toppings  - Gulab Jamun + syrup  - Crushed Pistachios - Crushed Rose Petals Combine wet and dry ingredients without overmixing, allowing small pockets of flour. Use a rubber or wooden spatula to mix the batter. Let it rest, then pour 1/2 cup of batter in the pan with generous amounts of butter. Flip until both sides are golden brown 🌹Pancakes are so much better when you add some desi twist to it.  #dessert #recipe #recipes #pancakes #gulabjamun

caramelized onion & herb buttered noodles!  Ingredients: 1/2 lb pasta 2 tbsp olive oil 2 yellow onions, sliced thin 1 tbsp fresh thyme 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar 1 stick butter, softened salt and pepper to taste as many fresh herbs as you want! (i used a small handful of basil, tarragon, chives, and parsley) Instructions: Heat oil in a large sauté pan over med/low heat. Add onions and cook for about 30 minutes or so, stirring occasionally until the onions are jammy and brown. Add thyme, balsamic vinegar, salt, and pepper. Stir (making sure to scape the bottom of the pan!) and let cook for a few more minutes, then set aside to cool. While onions cool, cook the pasta according to package instructions. Be sure to save some pasta water.  Add butter, caramelized onions, and whatever herbs you want to a food processor. Pulse until everything is well combined.  Toss the butter mixture with the cooked hot pasta and a little pasta water. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. Top with parm (optional but highly recommended) and enjoy. #caramelizedonions #pasta #easyrecipe #pastatok

Buttermilk Saffron pancakes with gulab jamun  🌹Dry Ingredients  - 1 1/3 cup of flour  - 1tsp salt  - 2 tbs sugar  - 1 tbs baking powder  - 1/2 tsp baking soda (for that rise) 🌹Wet ingredients  (Everything needs to be at room temp)  - 1 cup buttermilk / 1 cup milk + 1 tbs lemon juice (let it sit for 15 mins) - 8-10 Saffron soaked in the buttermilk  - 1 egg  - 4 tbs melted butter  - 0.25 tsp cardamom powder  🌹Toppings  - Gulab Jamun + syrup  - Crushed Pistachios - Crushed Rose Petals Combine wet and dry ingredients without overmixing, allowing small pockets of flour. Use a rubber or wooden spatula to mix the batter. Let it rest, then pour 1/2 cup of batter in the pan with generous amounts of butter. Flip until both sides are golden brown 🌹Pancakes are so much better when you add some desi twist to it.  #dessert #recipe #recipes #pancakes #gulabjamun

Hashbrown Bowl Meal Prep This recipe is so easy and it’s like having your own little egg casserole each day. Use class containers so you can cook it in the container. *i used 28 oz glass containers that are linked in my meal prep highlight* For four breakfasts: -10 eggs (you can add more if you’d like) -4 cups frozen shredded hash browns -1/2 cup cheese or choice  -8 mini precooked chicken breakfast sausages -salt, pepper, garlic powder, red pepper flakes -fresh chives  -optional: add a diced red pepper or a veggie of choice  1. Preheat oven to 350 2. Whisk together eggs with seasoning until well combined 3. Spray each individual glass container with avocado oil spray 4. Add 1 cup Hashbrowns to the bottom of each glass 5. Cut up chicken sausage and divide between four bowls (I sautéed mine for a little before to brown it but since they are precooked you can skip this step) 6. Divide eggs into four containers by pouring them over the Hashbrowns 7. Top with shredded cheese 8. Bake for 35 mins 9. After baking top with fresh chives 10. Enjoy for 4 days in fridge or freeze

Upside Down Tomato Burrata Tart Recipe 👇 Ingredients: 1 sheet of puff pastry, defrosted per package directions 3-4 small tomatoes, cut into ¼-inch slices Kosher salt Black pepper 2 tbsp basil, roughly chopped, plus more for garnish ½ cup @BelGioiosoCheese Freshly Shredded Parmesan Cheese 1 egg, lightly beaten 8 ounces BelGioiosoCheese burrata, torn into fourths Instructions: Lay tomato slices on paper towels, season both sides with salt and pepper, then cover with more paper towels. Set aside 15 minutes. Roll puff pastry out and cut into 4 even rectangles. Prick the surface with a fork. Set aside. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and create four mounds of chopped basil, 3-4 tomato slices, and 2 tbsp of shredded Parmesan. Top each with puff pastry, crimping the edges with a fork to affix it to the parchment paper. Brush the surface with egg. Bake 35-40 minutes at 400°F, or until golden brown. Let cool for 10 minutes before inverting onto a serving platter and peeling away the parchment. Top with spoonfuls of burrata and sprinkle on flaky sea salt and extra chopped basil.

To me, FEARLESS is living in spite of those things that scare you to death. FEARLESS is falling madly in love again, even though you’ve been hurt before. FEARLESS is walking into your freshmen year of high school at fifteen. FEARLESS is getting back up and fighting for what you want over and over again… even though every time you’ve tried before, you’ve lost. It’s FEARLESS to have faith that someday things will change. FEARLESS is having the courage to say goodbye to someone who only hurts you, even if you can’t breathe without them. I think it’s FEARLESS to fall for your best friend, even though he’s in love with someone else. And when someone apologizes to you enough times for things they’ll never stop doing, I think it’s FEARLESS to stop believing them. It’s FEARLESS to say “you’re NOT sorry”, and walk away. I think loving someone despite what people think is FEARLESS. I think allowing yourself to cry on the bathroom floor is FEARLESS. Letting go is FEARLESS. Then, moving on and being alright…That’sFEARLESS too. But no matter what love throws at you, you have to believe in it. You have to believe in love stories and prince charmings and happily ever after. That’s why I write these songs. Because I think love is FEARLESS.”  #taylorswift #taylorsversion #swiftietiktok #taylorswifttattoo #fearlesstv #fyp

This is the 1st episode of my new LAZY DINNER SERIES. Of course I am being sarcastic by using the word “lazy”. There is nothing lazy about putting a meal on the table, it’s always work. However in this series I aim to reduce the prep work and the time you spend in the kitchen. Baking dish: @juliskaofficial  Lazy Chicken Dinner Ingredients 10 pieces of chicken breast, THINLY sliced (can sub with chicken thighs) 1/3 cup + 2 Tbsp olive oil 1/4 cup grated cheese 2 tsp crushed Calabrian jarred chili 1/2 tsp salt  3 cloves garlic grated 1 lemon juiced 1/2 tsp oregano 1 cup Italian seasoned breadcrumbs 3 tbsp melted butter 1 loaf of sliced bread Tomato Salad Ingredients 3 large tomatoes 1/4 red onion sliced thin 1/4 cup fresh basil 3 tbsp olive oil 1 tbsp red wine vinegar 1/2 tsp salt Lazy Chicken  -Preheat oven to 375F -To a large baking sheet add, olive oil, grated cheese, Calabrian chili pepper, salt, garlic, lemon juice and oregano. Use a fork or small whisk to mix the ingredients.  -Coat each chicken piece in the mixture as shown. -To a medium sized bowl add Italian seasoned breadcrumbs and melted butter. Mix well. WARNING! Most pre seasoned breadcrumbs contain salt. Adding any additional salt will make the dish too salty. -Top each piece of chicken with the breadcrumb mix and bake for 20 minutes or until the chicken has an internal temp of 165F. Cook time may be slightly longer or shorter depending on the thickness of your chicken. If you want crispier breadcrumbs, broil for the last 2 minutes max. Lazy Tomato Salad -Remove the stem and slice tomatoes into wedges -Use a mandoline to slice the red onion. Please don’t do as I do! Use the mandoline guard . -Add olive oil, red wine vinegar and salt. Mix well then top with fresh basil. DO NOT MIX IN THE BASIL UNTIL YOU ARE READY TO SERVE. #chickendinner #easydinner #easydinnerrecipes #easyrecipe #quickrecipes #chickenrecipe

one pot broccoli cheddar pasta 🥦🧀🥦🧀 easy, cheesy, and kind of nostalgic-y because of the spaghettios vibe  recipe: 2 tbsp butter 1 tbsp olive oil 2 cloves garlic, minced 1 shallot, minced  1 medium carrot, shredded (about 3/4 cup shredded) 2 cups broccoli 2 cups anelli pasta 4 cups water or broth 1/2 tsp paprika 1/2 tsp black pepper 1/2 tsp garlic powder salt to taste 1/2 cup heavy cream 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese Melt butter and oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add shallot and garlic and cook until fragrant. Add carrot and pasta and cook for a couple minutes. Add water (or broth) and spices and bring to a boil. Turn down the heat to a simmer and cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until most of the water is absorbed. Add broccoli, heavy cream, and cheese, stir until the cheese is melted. Continue to cook for about 5 more minutes, until pasta is al dente and sauce is thick. Serve immediately.  #pasta #broccolicheddar #easyrecipe #pastatok

caramelized onion & herb buttered noodles!  Ingredients: 1/2 lb pasta 2 tbsp olive oil 2 yellow onions, sliced thin 1 tbsp fresh thyme 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar 1 stick butter, softened salt and pepper to taste as many fresh herbs as you want! (i used a small handful of basil, tarragon, chives, and parsley) Instructions: Heat oil in a large sauté pan over med/low heat. Add onions and cook for about 30 minutes or so, stirring occasionally until the onions are jammy and brown. Add thyme, balsamic vinegar, salt, and pepper. Stir (making sure to scape the bottom of the pan!) and let cook for a few more minutes, then set aside to cool. While onions cool, cook the pasta according to package instructions. Be sure to save some pasta water.  Add butter, caramelized onions, and whatever herbs you want to a food processor. Pulse until everything is well combined.  Toss the butter mixture with the cooked hot pasta and a little pasta water. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. Top with parm (optional but highly recommended) and enjoy. #caramelizedonions #pasta #easyrecipe #pastatok

Protein cake is a liv bday staple 🤌🏼👩‍🍳💋 Recipe:  (Cake) ✰ 1/2 cup 0% Greek yogurt ✰ 1 cup applesauce ✰ 1/2 cup sweetener (I used monkfruit) ✰ 2 eggs  ✰ 1 tsp cake batter extract ✰ 2/3 cup flour  ✰ 1 scoop 1st Phorm Level-1 Protein in Vanilla Ice Cream (link in bio :)) ✰ 1 tsp baking soda ✰ pinch salt (Frosting) ✰ 1 cup 0% fat Greek yogurt ✰ 3/4 scoop 1st Phorm Level-1 Protein in Vanilla Ice Cream (link in bio :)) ✰ 1/2 tsp bday cake extract  ✰ 1/4 tbsp powdered sugar (I used monkfruit) ✰ 1 tsp sf jello pudding mix (optional makes it thicker) (Optional sprinkles for topping) – 1. Preheat oven to 350 F. 2. Mix wet (yogurt, applesauce, sweetener, egg, vanilla) with dry (flour, protein, baking soda, and salt). 3. Bake for around 18-20 min or until toothpick comes out clean (do not over bake or fudginess will be ruined). 4. Combine ingredients for frosting. 5. Cut edges of cake.  6. Assemble layers.  7. Combine edges and leftover frosting, form balls and top cake.  8. Enjoy!  - (1/10 servings) Nutrition: cals 90 fat 1.5g carb 11g protein 7.5g my cake: 896 cals 16g fat 109g carb 75g protein  milk bar cake: 7692 cals 420g fat 888g carb 60g protein

🌯 Just whipped up my own version of the plant-based crunchwrap, and it’s a game-changer! #ad Using plant-based ingredients like @LightLife Smart Ground keeps me feeling powered up. You can find LightLife plant-based proteins in the refrigerated produce aisles of your local grocery store! #plantbasedrecipes #plantbasedcrumbles #plantbased Plant-Based Taco Meat 1 tbsp avocado oil 1 small red onion, minced 12 oz package LightLife Smart Ground 1 veggie bouillon cube, crushed 2 tbsp nutritional yeast 2 tbsp taco seasoning 1 tsp smoked paprika Guacamole 1 avocado Juice of half a lime 2 tbsp minced red onion 2 tbsp diced tomatoes 2 tbsp minced cilantro For Assembly 2 tsp avocado oil 3 corn tortillas 4 large burrito-size tortillas 6-8 tbsp cashew nacho cheese 2 plum tomatoes, diced 2 cups shredded lettuce Salt to taste Preheat oven to 400F. Brush the corn tortillas with some oil then place on a parchment lined baking tray. Bake for 4 mins, flip then bake again for 3-4 mins.  To a large skillet add oil and heat over medium heat. When hot, add onions and saute with a pinch of salt until softened. Stir in the grounds and saute for 3-4 mins until it browns evenly. Add remaining seasonings and bouillon. Saute until fully mixed and fragrant. To a medium bowl add the avocado and mash. Add lime, tomatoes, onion, cilantro and a pinch of salt and fold together. Assemble. Warm a large tortilla and place on a flat surface. Spread the center with cheese sauce then top with crumbles followed by the crispy tortilla, then lettuce and diced tomato. Carefully top with guacamole, then using an extra tortilla, cut into quarters and use one piece to place on top. Heat up a skillet while you fold your wrap. Grab one side of the tortilla and pull it up towards the center. Continue folding up the sides until you have a hexagon shape. Place the wrap seam side down in the skillet. Cook for 2-3 mins, flip and repeat until golden. Remove, cut in half and enjoy! EASY BEEF BULGOLGI MEAL PREP So easy to make and literally packed full of flavor! All you need is 👇🏻 - 1lb thinly sliced sirloin or ribeye (I am using frozen “quick steak” for this) - 1/2 cup coconut aminos or soy - 2-3 green onions finely chopped - 1 tbsp garlic - 1 tbsp ginger - 2 tsp sesame oil - 1/4 cup brown sugar (a brown sugar substitute or honey) - 1 tbsp rice vinegar - Water (If necessary - I will use to thin out the marinade to fully submerge the meat!) 1. If you are chopping your own sirloin - freeze it for a little before slicing so that you can slice it super thin!  2. Finely chop green onions, mince garlic and grate ginger. 3. In a large bowl add (thawed) sirloin, chopped green onions, ginger, garlic, sesame oil, brown sugar, rice vinegar and water if necessary to completely submerge the meat in the marinade. 4. Marinate meat for 2-4 hours. 5. Either throw bulgogi in air fryer (I do this on broil for 5-10 minutes just check every few minutes and flip halfway) or place bulgogi in a super hot pan and do not move it around at all for at least 2 minutes to let the bulgogi crisp up a bit. (Also I highly recommend doing this in batches so you don’t over crowd the pan) 6. After 2 minutes flip bulgogi and mix around and then let sit again for another 4-5 minutes or until bulgogi is a little crispy and fully cooked. This should take about 10 minutes max.  7. Serve with mixture of white/cauliflower rice, kimchi, and cucumber salad and enjoy :) #bulgolgi #mealprep #highprotein #easyrecipe

gonna switch it up this time yall, favorite song is going first. todays song is "saturday satan, sunday saint" specifcally by charley crockett or ernest tubb this song feels good in my soul, it speaks to a piece that is in all of us. listen to its words and its tubby bass and think of what they mean to you these were the last videos i took before it all fell apart. one month ago i got back from my overnight bouldering trip up in tramway. i climbed hard for 2 days, sent my first roof v3, backpacked 3 miles in complete darkness, slept in my hammock for the first time, it was a great trip with a good friend. the day after i got back from my trip i decided to hangout with some other friends at the gym. i hadnt rested one bit since my trip and immediately got back go trying my crimpy v6 problem, sent that and went to go cool down on a v3 and on that climb i partially ruptured my A4 pulley in my right ring finger. i went to the doctor the next day and had it looked at and was basically told i couldnt climb for 1-2 months. i had to stop cold turkey. naturally i didnt listen and only gave myself 1 week till i started trying at a new v7 in my gym. my second time back in the gym and i strained the middle tendon in my left hand. another hand injury, barely a week from the last. this crushed me, now i knew i had to stop entirely or else i might do something really bad and never be able to climb again. this last month has been one of the hardest ina couple years. both of my cats are dying, im working a demeaning job, im having car issues, and now the one outlet i have is gone. the one thing i truly love to do has to be put on hold. ive been recovering slowly, the rehab ive been doing has helped immensely. i think i might be able to start projecting again and climbing outdoors come the end of september. i just miss rock climbing so much, having to hold yourseld back from your passion is painful and harms nearly every other aspect of my life. its just been really hard to get through it all when i cant even grab some rock or plastic go make it all go away for a time. i miss my friends and i wish i made more money. all i wanna do is be happy and climb, i dont understand why that has to be so hard in this world. todays poem is formed as a question but be real yall, you know the answer: what is my body if not the form to experience pleasure through? what is my body if not a tool to create and experience this world? what is my body if not a vessel, free to express and to truly live what is it then?

Steam Your Bed for Bed Bugs Before and After Traveling Steaming your bed is a great way to prevent bed bugs from hitching a ride on your clothes or luggage. Steam kills bed bugs and their eggs, so it's an effective way to reduce the risk of bringing bed bugs home with you after traveling. To steam your bed, you will need a steam cleaner that can produce steam at least 160°F. You can also use a handheld steamer or a garment steamer. Once you have your steam cleaner, follow these steps: 1. Remove all bedding and pillows from the bed. 2. Steam the mattress, box spring, and frame. 3. Steam the bed frame, headboard, and footboard. 4. Steam the nightstands and any other furniture in the room. 5. Steam your clothes and luggage. Pecan Apple Crisp for One 🍏 Apple Base 1 medium apple, cubed, peeled if you want (sub peach, or pear) 1 tablespoon pecan pieces (optional) 2 tablespoons sugar 1  tablespoon melted butter 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon  1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg (optional) Crisp Topping 2 tablespoons butter, softened 2 tablespoons brown sugar  2 tablespoons flour 3 tablespoons rolled oats  1/4 teaspoon cinnamon  Tiny pinch of salt  Optional Ice cream or whipped cream  Caramel sauce  1. Chop apple into bite sized pieces. Combine all of the apple base ingredients in mug/dish and stir until well mixed.  2. In a separate dish, combine the topping ingredients and mix with fork.  3. Add topping to the mug apple base and microwave for 3-3 1/2 minutes until bubbly.  4. Let cool for 5 minutes.  5. Top with ice cream and a drizzle of caramel sauce.  Notes: if you have the energy, peeled apples are a little better!  Making two: I suggest just following the recipe, but in two mugs, vs doubling the ingredients all together.  #fallrecipes #easyrecipes #fallaesthetic #fallthings #fallvibes #autumnaesthetic #mycozyhome #cozyvibes  #kitchendecor #dessertrecipe #dessertideas #falltok #falltiktok

Recipe:  🧀 1 cup cottage cheese  🧀 1 cup shredded cheese  🌾 1 cup gluten free flour (I used @bobsredmill  1 to 1)  🥚2 eggs  🧂 salt, oregano, or other seasonings to taste  1. Mix all ingredients together  2. Scoop onto a sheet and top with salt or seasonings  3. Bake at 375 for 15-30 min or until golden brown  4. Slather on your fave toppings and eat them in bed or in the tub or wherever makes you the most happy. creamy, high-protein mac & cheese with no roux or fancy cheeses — you don’t even have to drain the pasta. inspired by a @Serious Eats recipe 🧀 what you need: 6 ounces pasta (1 3/4 cups)   1/2 cup whipped whole milk cottage cheese 2-4 ounces sharp cheddar cheese (1/2-1 cup) what to do: Add pasta to pot or skillet and add just enough water to cover. Add a pinch of salt; bring to boil. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pasta is almost al dente, about 6 min. Add cottage cheese and cheddar (I used 2 oz but it can handle more!), lower heat, cook until creamy sauce forms. Season w/ salt and lots of black pepper. serves 2.  #cottagecheese #highprotein #macandcheese

GARLIC GIRL RED SAUCE!! Realized I’ve never told you about the tomato sauce recipe I swear by! It’s got 20 cloves of garlic but you can add more to your heart’s desire!!! Made this batch for another recipe dropping soon that I cannotttttt wait for you to see, but until then it’s time for a pasta party bb!!!! Garlic Girl Red Sauce Makes about 6 cups 1/4 cup olive oil 20 garlic cloves, smashed and peeled 1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped 1 (6-ounce) can tomato paste 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper 1 cup red wine 1 (28-ounce) can crushed tomatoes  1 tablespoon granulated sugar, plus more to taste 1 teaspoon dried oregano Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper Herb bundle of 2 sprigs each basil, thyme, and bay leaves tied together with butcher’s twine In a medium pot or Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the garlic and onion and cook until softened and begin to caramelize, 5 to 6 minutes. Add the tomato paste and crushed red pepper and cook until beginning to caramelize, about 2 minutes, then stir in the red wine and crushed tomatoes. Season with the sugar, oregano, and two heavy pinches each of salt and pepper. Nestle in the herb bundle, then cover and cook for 30 minutes, reducing the heat to medium-low. Remove from the heat, discard the herb bundle, and purée the sauce with an immersion blender. Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt, pepper, and sugar. Use immediately or cool and store in airtight containers in the refrigerator for up to 1 week or the freezer for up to 6 months.  #garlic #tomatosauce #sauce

Here’s a couple reasons why I recommend taking the Amtrak train to New orleans for Mardi Gras.  1. Price is unbeatable. During Mardi Gras flights can range from $300 to $500. Taking the Amtrak made it more affordable for us.  2. Free checked bags, we could bring as much luggage as we needed.  3. Planes can be uncomfortable. During this trip we had lots of space & leg room!!  4. You were able to bring your own food like many others or buy something from their menu. 5. The vibes on the train were amazing. It was such a frindly environment. I felt alot of southern love and hospitality on the train. Everyone (from strangers to friends) talked and dance with eachother the whole ride.  6. The whole ride we were able to see some amazing views.  #fyp #cheaptravel #amtrak #neworleans #mardigras

Today I tried one of my dream fruits- peanut butter fruit!! If you’ve been following me for a while, I made a list sometime back of all of my dream fruits to try! This was the last one I had to find on that particular list so now it’s time for me to make a new one!  My friend @jeanfruitbeast harvested these in South Florida! I absolutely love peanut butter and have been dying to know if these fruits actually taste like it. Some of the fruits I’ve tried have not met up to the expectations from their names.  The peanut butter fruits I got were perfectly ripened to eat. They almost looks like little blistered tomatoes, which made me a little bit nervous because I am allergic to tomatoes 😂 the pulp, and the skin are both edible, and there are large seeds in the middle that you cannot eat. I am super stoked to report that the flavor tasted like a mix of figs, pumpkin and of course peanut butter!!! it was the perfect mix of all of those flavors. The texture was jammy almost like pumpkin purée! This fruit far exceeded my expectations 🥹 #rarefruit #peanutbutterfruit #fruittok

I am so excited to show you all lobster mushrooms!! These are mushrooms that are attacked by a parasite that turns the mushrooms this beautiful orange color- nature is awesome! So they do have a little bit of a fishy smell they do not taste like lobster, even though the color resembles it!  I really wanted to make a pasta blanket type of vibe for these. I started off my cleaning the mushrooms- come at me all you want but I do not like biting into anything sandy. I then cooked the mushrooms in salted butter with shallots, garlic, and garlic scapes!  For the sauce I whipped ricotta with olive oil, salt, and oregano. I got really good ricotta that turned perfectly silky when whipped 😩😮‍💨 I used an egg and Seminola lasagna sheet cut in half to make the pasta “blanket”  I then added a layer of those mushrooms, whipped ricotta, the cooked garlic mixture, brown butter toasted pine nuts, olive oil, and salt to the bowl. Then I tucked that in with the pasta blanket (I tossed that in the mushroom butter too for extra flavor). Finally I topped the pasta with poached sea beans, more whipped ricotta, a mushroom, pecorino cheese, pink peppercorns, salt, and olive oil. This was so freaking delicious I wish I could share a bite with all of you 🫶🏻 #lobstermushrooms #mushrooms #vegetarian

Salt Cured Key Lime! 🍋 I LOVE key lime- and there are some really important differences when it comes to taste, texture, and acidity when working with them!  - Key limes are less tart than a regular lime, but with beautiful floral undertones- a great way to describe them is aromatic. This is what gives key lime pie it’s distinct flavor that really can’t be replicated!  - Key limes have a thinner skin and less pith than a traditional lime which is why they work in salt curing. It’s much the same as the difference between lemons and Meyer lemons! - Key limes are more acidic than regular limes. This helps them stay fresh when preserved longer, but it’s harder to keep them out on the counter because the skin will dehydrate more quickly! To Preserve: Layer a clean jar with salt and halved key limes with blossom and stem end removed. Macerating between each layer to release juice. Cover and leave on the counter for three days and then transfer to be refrigerated for up to six months! #foodpreservation #urbanhomestead #keylime #citrus #preservedlemons #sustainability #slowliving #zerowaste #lowwaste #denver #citrusrecipes #healthyliving

This Lazy Trader Joe’s Cili Onion Hummus Pasta is a winner. It’s got a hint of spice, and adding baby broccoli rounds the flavors out perfectly. Here’s everything you need:  16 oz TJ’s Organic Pasta Quintet  10 oz TJ’s Chili Onion Hummus 8 oz Baby Broccoli, chopped  1 tbsp TJ’s Crunchy Chili Onion Oil ¼ cup Reserved Pasta Water Salt and Pepper to Taste Chili Onion Peanuts, Chopped (optional, for garnish) Prepare pasta according to package instructions—reserve ¼ cup of the pasta water and set aside.  As the pasta cooks, heat a medium pan over medium heat. Add in the baby broccoli and crunchy onion chili oil. Cook for 5-7 minutes and set aside.  Drain the pasta and add it back to the pot. Add in the chili onion hummus and broccoli rabe. Slowly add in the pasta water and mix until it reaches your desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.  Garnish with chili onion peanuts if you’d like and enjoy!  #lazytraderjoesmeals #vegan #foodie

I made morel mushroom “dumplings” stuffed with iberico pork and I couldn’t wait to show you all!! This was technically so difficult, but it turned out better than I could’ve ever imagined 😭 I got these massive morels and I knew from the moment I saw them they had to be stuffed! I wanted to pair the morels with iberico pork because iberico eats similar to wagyu beef but tastes like pork. I cut the pork into small chunks to really get that melt in your mouth pork texture that makes iberico pork so special!  I seasoned the pork with soybean paste, garlic scapes, sesame oil, mirin, morels, garlic, ginger, and shallots. I let the meat season then soaked the morels in salted water for 5 minutes! I made a sauce to poach the morels in using butter, soy sauce, a lot of mirin, and sesame oil!  I pan fried the pork in a little bit of butter until it got color. Then I poached the morel mushrooms in the butter sauce for one minute each, until the outer skin gets soft. I then let the mushrooms cool off- as they cook the mushroom liquid starts to seep out into the inside of the mushrooms adding extra flavor for the filling!  I added the iberico pork into the morels then let that set for a few minutes. I was really nervous to pipe the filling in because morels rip really easily! Once the filling was set I pan tried the mushrooms to get a little bit of color. I legit almost cried at how perfect these turned out. I added some black sesame seeds, a poached garlic scape, and spicy coconut vinegar to garnish the little morel “dumplings” with! I wish you all could try these because my vision came through a million times better than I was expecting ❤️ #morelmushrooms #ibericopork #dumplings

Fried feta with honey (feta Saganaki) filled a hole in my heart that I didn’t even know I had 😭 Recipe below!!  ingredients:  -block of feta (in the brine)   -1/2 puff pastry sheet  -sesame seeds  -olive oil  -honey  -flour (for rolling the pastry)  Recipe:  -slice feta block into even slices. you can make it as thick as you want.  -roll pastry sheet out on floured surface until thin. Cut into 4 squares  -wrap feta in puff pastry, brush on some feta brine to the top and roll in sesame seeds.  -heat olive oil in a cast iron on med heat. Add feta and cook until it puffs up and both sides are golden brown  -immediately add to a paper towel lined plate. I can’t believe I’m saying this, but I might like fried pickle dip better than french onion dip. Try it and you be the judge! Fried Pickle Dip 1/2-3/4 cup panko crumbs 1 tbsp unsalted butter 1 cup whipped cream cheese 1 cup sour cream 1 cup fresh dill pickles, finely diced + some for garnish 1-2 tbsp ranch seasoning 1/2 tsp onion powder 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice 2 cloves garlic, grated 2 tbsp fresh dill, chopped + some to garnish 2 tbsp fresh chive, chopped + some to garnish Salt and pepper to taste Over medium heat, melt butter in a frying pan then add the panko crumbs, lightly toss in butter and toast until golden. Remove from heat to cool and set aside 2 tbsp to garnish.  To a bowl, add remaining ingredients and mix to combine. If consistency is thicker than your preference, add tbsp of pickle juice and lemon juice. Allow to chill for at least 30 minutes. Add garnish, serve with potato chips or pretzels and enjoy! #recipes #appetizers #dips #pickles #friedpickledip

When a recipe calls for one clove of garlic this is what it means 😂❤️‍🔥 Today I got to try solo garlic! It occurs naturally alongside elephant garlic when the cloves don’t split creating this giant epic garlic clove- which is really cool if you ask me 🤓 I did a garlic confit with some herbs to start off because confit garlic is my favorite way to enjoy garlic! Solo garlic when cooked of soft, creamy with a sweet garlicky flavor! I decided it would go perfectly with crabs! I got snowcrab legs and had the idea to make a solo garlic buttery snowcrab roll! For the bread I toasted a baguette in salted butter then I made a lemony whipped ricotta with a little bit of solo garlic oil!  I then added a thiccc layer of mashed solo garlic, the whipped ricotta, then cold crab into the baguette. I kept the crab cold because I got it cooked and wanted it to have the fresh flavor! I then topped the crab with melted salted butter, Zataar seasoning, and chives! This was so delicious 😍 #sologarlic #garlicgirl #crab

Recipe: - in an oven safe pot, saute 1c onion & carrots (all measurements are a guess - use as much as you’d like) - add 1lb cubed chicken breast and 2tsp of butter - add 2c chopped mini potatoes and 1c corn - submerge everything in chicken broth (i think i used about 4c) and simmer for 10-15min - thicken with a flour paste (flour + water). Stir it into the pot pie mix and repeat as necessary until it reaxhes desired thickness   - add 1/3c heavy cream and 1/3c Parmesan and mix - top with buttermilk biscuits  - bake accoring to instructions (ours was 400 degrees for 12-15min) - let cool and enjoy! #onepotmeals #chickenpotpie #dutchovencooking #easyrecipe #weeknightdinner #easymeal #familymeal #recipesoftiktok

A little more “behind the recipe” on this ground beef pasta. Would you want to hear more behind the scenes type stuff about recipe blogging? One pot Philly cheesesteak pasta with ground beef, sweet onions, green peppers, cream cheese, and provolone cheese is an easy dinner recipe. INGREDIENTS  2 tablespoons olive oil 1 pound ground beef 1 large sweet onion sliced 1 green bell pepper sliced or diced 0.87 ounce brown gravy mix 8 ounces penne pasta 3 cups beef broth 4 ounces cream cheese softened and cubed 6 ounces provolone cheese slices chopped Salt and pepper to taste Fresh parsley chopped (optional) DIRECTIONS  1️⃣ In a large pot or Dutch, add olive oil over medium-high heat. When warm, add the ground beef to the skillet and cook until browned, breaking it up into smaller pieces with a spatula. 2️⃣ When the meat is nearly brown, add the sliced onions and diced green bell pepper and cook, stirring occasionally for 3-5 minutes. Drain any excess grease from the pot. 3️⃣ Add the brown gravy mix and stir to coat the beef and veggies. 4️⃣ Add the uncooked pasta and pour the beef broth over top, giving it a good stir. Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cover the pot and let it simmer for about 12-15 minutes, or until the pasta is cooked to al dente, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking. 5️⃣ Once the pasta is cooked, uncover the pot and add the softened cream cheese and the chopped provolone cheese slices. Stir into the cooked pasta to distribute. Cover the pot again and let it sit for a few minutes, allowing the heat to melt the cheese 6️⃣ Remove the lid and stir to distribute the melted cheese evenly. Taste and adjust the seasoning if needed. Garnish with fresh parsley (optional). #groundbeefrecipe #groundbeefpasta #cheesesteakpasta #easyrecipe #comfortfoodrecipe #onepotmeals #onepotpasta

Unpopular opinion: I love the cottage cheese trend Not because I think every single food needs to be “healthified”, but because I genuinely think it’s such a cool, versatile way to make some higher protein foods and snacks! Is this the same thing as authentic queso you’ll find at your fave Mexican restaurant? Ummm no lol but it’s a great high protein yummy dip idea and it’s SO simple! Grab the full recipe at www.thebalancednutritionist.com/cottage-cheese-queso or get the cliff notes here: INGREDIENTS 16 oz Cottage cheese 1 can diced green chilis 1 clove garlic 1 cup Mexican shredded cheese INSTRUCTIONS Add cottage cheese, shredded cheese, diced green chilis and garlic clove to a high-speed blender or food processor. Blend on high until the queso dip is smooth and creamy. Taste test and add salt, pepper, or any additional seasonings to taste. Enjoy as a cold dip or microwave slowly in 15 second increments until hot. Stir in between microwave sessions. **IMPORTANT**: If you microwave the queso for too long or too quickly, it will separate- heat carefully until it's just warm enough so that the queso stays nice and creamy! Cottage Cheese Vodka Pasta Kosher salt 1 pound dried pasta 2 tablespoons olive oil 1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped  6 garlic cloves, thinly sliced 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper  1 (6-ounce) can tomato paste 1/2 cup vodka 1 pound low-fat cottage cheese, at room temperature  Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add your pasta and cook until al dente, according to box directions. Drain, reserving 1 cup pasta water.  Meanwhile in a high-sided skillet, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic, then season with the crushed red pepper and 2 heavy pinches of salt. Cook until the onion begins to brown 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 2 minutes, then stir in the vodka. Reduce the heat to medium, then cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.  Transfer the tomato mixture to a blender with the cottage cheese and purée until smooth.  Return the sauce back to the pan off the heat with the drained pasta, 1/2 cup reserved pasta water, and 2 heavy pinches of salt. Stir until well coated, adding more pasta water if needed. Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt, then serve.  #pasta #cottagecheese #protein

Liang Fen (Mung Bean Jelly Noodles) 1 part mung bean starch (1/4 cup or 65g per person) 6 parts water (7 for softer texture) 1 Tbsp soy sauce 1 tsp Chinese black vinegar 1/2 tsp toasted sesame oil pinch of sugar 1 Tbsp chili oil sliced scallions and ground Sichuan peppercorn for garnish 1. In a mixing bowl, combine the mung bean starch and half the water.  2. In a saucepan, heat the remaining water until barely simmering. Stir in the mung bean starch slurry and continue to cook, stirring constantly. Cook until the mixture begins to turn translucent and boils with large bubbles, about 3 to 4 minutes. Carefully pour into a baking dish or heat-safe container. Let cool completely at room temperature for at least 2 hours. Once cool, you can pour a thin layer of water on top of the noodles to keep from drying out. 3. To serve, combine all the sauce ingredients in a small bowl and stir well. Cut the block of noodles into strips or cubes. Drizzle with the sauce and chili oil, then sprinkle with scallions and Sichuan peppercorn. #storytime #lunch #liangfen #noodles

Lets catch up! After limewashing the bedroom walls, the door install was next.  Changing out the doors in our home has been on my list for awhile, but I haven't found any main doors that I love, so I settled to change out just the bathroom door in the room to open up the space & make it look less like a builder grade.  So off we went to find the the tools we needed, and to both of our surprise, there's literally door install tool kits to complete the task. Altogether we needed 4 kits and we used only 3 others tools we had such as our drill, router, and wood chisel.  It took less than a day to install, but the staining made the switch-a-roo a bit more complicated and I didn't finish the door until a couple weeks later after 3 tries. I ended up sanding the door, using prestain, then applying Behr Tamarind and coating it with a polyurethane to seal. . . #doorinstall #bedroomdesign #bedroommakeover #bedroominspo #bedroominteriors #diyprojects

I literally didn’t even own any tools, know how to use a saw, or how switch a light fixture. But I started even when I was scared. I asked for help when I could. I’ve gotten some serious criticism since sharing Maisy's litter of pups (to the point I didn’t even want to share their cuteness). I’ve had people message me saying their living conditions are “dirty” or it’s “cruel” to MAKE Maisy and her puppies live outside— I should bring them inside or kennel Maisy and the pups up. It would cause unnecessary stress for Maisy inside or in a kennel. She was bred to be outside with her sheep.  Freedom vs. risk... that's what I think about when it comes to my livestock and guardian dogs. Every rancher/farmer gets to decide what works for them. I believe that wildness is at the heart of everything good for animals. It's because of this that I choose more freedom AND more risk.  This doesn’t mean I don’t care or attend to my livestock or the guardian dogs. Even so, I can't eliminate every bit of risk and discomfort that sometimes (rarely) comes with their pasture life.  So it may seem cruel or dirty, but it’s as natural as it gets for Maisy. I’ve learned to be okay with the risks when they arise.  On another note, it’s so fucking cool to see her build a den under a woodrats nest!  ——————————— For those that don’t know the Great Pyrenees, we’re bred to be livestock guardian dogs in the mountains of Europe and have been used effectively for centuries to guard livestock.
